The paper deals with the problem of understanding diagrams and images using natural image understanding approaches, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also introduces a structured prediction model that incorporates convolutional neural networks, which is a common technique used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The model also involves global normalization and matching constraints, which are techniques used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.AI, and cs.LG, followed by cs.CL and cs.IR.
